A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 County Boards of Education – Volunteer Aides – School Chaplain
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing each county board of education to use a chaplain as a
4 volunteer aide in schools to provide services to students; and generally relating to
5 county boards of education and volunteer aides.
6 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
7 Article – Education
8 Section 6–106
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Education
14 6–106.
15 (a) (1) Each county board may use volunteer aides in school activities in its
16 county.
17 (2) A COUNTY BOARD MAY USE A CHAPLAIN AS A VOLUNTEER AIDE IN
18 SCHOOLS TO PROVIDE SUPPORT SERVICES TO STUDENTS.
19 (b) A volunteer aide may not be used to supplant educational personnel but shall
20 be used to assist regular employees in their assignments.
21 (c) Each county superintendent shall establish guidelines for the use of volunteer
22 aides in the school system of the superintendent’s county.
